-- MBIA board member resigns to consult on project
-- 
-- Wed Mar 12, 2008 12:06pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/03/12/us-bonds-insurers-mbia-perry-idUSN1219875920080312

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Bond insurer MBIA Inc ( MBI.N ) said on Wednesday that Debra Perry, a director and former chief credit officer at a ratings agency, is resigning her position and will work as a risk management consultant to the company. 

 Perry is working on helping the board of directors and Chief Executive Jay Brown refine and implement its risk strategy, MBIA said. Perry worked at Moody's Corp from 1992 to 2004, where she held positions including chief credit officer and chief administrative officer. (Reporting by  Dan Wilchins ; editing by John Wallace)